	<preparation>** For Chicken:  

Marinate chicken in buttermilk for about 1 hour in frefrigerator.  Combine the flour, dried thyme and Creole seasoning in a bowl for dredging.  Drain the chicken and dredge in flour mixture, shaking off any excess.

Fry chicken in 350F oil for 9-10 minutes or until golden brown.  Complete the cooking by placing chicken in a 350F oven until chicken is cooked through, about ten minutes -- the juices will run clear.

Serve with Garlic Mashed Potatoes, yo!</preparation>
